    "body": "### Problem\n\n`vim._extui` does not play well with some vim plugins that uses the cmdline, e.g. [vim-easyalign](https://github.com/junegunn/vim-easy-align).\n\nWhen using vim-easyalign with `vim._extui` enabled, the \":EasyAlign (_)\" prompt will not be shown in the message area.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create the following `minimal.lua` file:\n    ```lua\n    vim\n      .system({\n        'git',\n        'clone',\n        '--depth=1',\n        '--filter=blob:none',\n        'https://github.com/junegunn/vim-easy-align.git',\n      })\n      :wait()\n\n    require('vim._extui').enable({})\n\n    vim.opt.rtp:append('vim-easy-align')\n    vim.keymap.set(\n      { 'n', 'x' },\n      'gl',\n      '<Plug>(EasyAlign)',\n      { noremap = false, desc = 'Align text' }\n    )\n    ```\n2. Run nvim with `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\n3. Open a random non-empty file\n4. Select a paragraph with >2 lines and hit `gl` to trigger align\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n\":EasyAlign (_)\" prompt should appear in the message area.\n\nWithout extui enabled the \":EasyAlign (_)\" prompt is shown normally, but with extui the prompt is not shown in the message area.\n\nWithout extui:\n\n<img width=\"1060\" height=\"599\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/75ff50bb-0ce8-4eb7-a20b-420689bd7617\" />\n\nWith extui:\n\n<img width=\"1061\" height=\"600\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6b7ffee9-1b1f-4442-8cdf-aa73c191aea7\" />\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-1574+g8d6963a6a0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n6.17.7-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.16.1 (42f49eeb) + tmux 3.5a\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
