            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Found a minimum repro @luukvbaal \n\n1. Create `minimal.vim` with the following lines:\n\n    ```vim\n    lua << EOF\n    if vim.env.NVIM_ENABLE_EXTUI then\n      require('vim._extui').enable({})\n    end\n    EOF\n\n    let tokens = [['Function', ':EasyAlign'], ['ModeMsg', ''], ['None', ' '], ['Comment', '('], ['Number', ''], ['Identifier', ''], ['Normal', '_'], ['Comment', ')'], ['Statement', '']]\n\n    function! s:echon_(tokens)\n      \" http://vim.wikia.com/wiki/How_to_print_full_screen_width_messages\n      let xy = [&ruler, &showcmd]\n      try\n        set noruler noshowcmd\n\n        let winlen = winwidth(winnr()) - 2\n        let len = len(join(map(copy(a:tokens), 'v:val[1]'), ''))\n        let ellipsis = len > winlen ? '..' : ''\n\n        echon \"\\r\"\n        let yet = 0\n        for [hl, msg] in a:tokens\n          if empty(msg) | continue | endif\n          execute \"echohl \". hl\n          let yet += len(msg)\n          if yet > winlen - len(ellipsis)\n            echon msg[ 0 : (winlen - len(ellipsis) - yet - 1) ] . ellipsis\n            break\n          else\n            echon msg\n          endif\n        endfor\n      finally\n        echohl None\n        let [&ruler, &showcmd] = xy\n      endtry\n    endfunction\n\n    call s:echon_(tokens)\n    let c = getchar()\n    ```\n\n2. Start nvim with `NVIM_ENABLE_EXTUI= nvim --clean -u minimal.vim`, you can see\n   the prompt \"EasyAlign (_)\" in the cmdline\n3. Now start nvim with extui enabled: `NVIM_ENABLE_EXTUI=1 nvim --clean -u minimal.vim`, the prompt is not shown.\n",
